dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Development. Division of Geology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 36 (1945) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief shown by 10 ft. (5 ft. in Cape May Co.) contour intervals and spot heights. Depths shown by 10 ft. contour and soundings in feet at mean or half tide. Inset: eastward continuation of map. Original survey 1883-4. Title was not given. Region covered: parts of Atlantic and Cape May counties. Original survey, 1883-4; principal features revised, 1916, 1933. Original survey and revisions made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer, revision of 1933 by R. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1945.
